---
import { Page, Block, Code } from '../../components/DocPage.js';
import { Event, EventListener } from '../../components/Links.js';
---

<Page title="event-capture">
  <Block>
    <p>The <strong>event-capture</strong> longhand property specifies if the event should be handled in the <a href="https://www.w3.org/TR/DOM-Level-3-Events/#event-flow">capture phase</a> of event ordering.</p>
    <p>event-capture is a longhand version of the <Event /> shorthand's 2nd argument.</p>
  </Block>
  <section>
    <h2>Example</h2>
    <Block>
      <p>In this example, the longhand event-capture is used with <EventListener /> to specify that the event should be handled in the capture phase.</p>
      <Code slot="code" lang="css" code={`
.outer {
  event-listener: click var(--close-modal);
  event-capture: click true;
}
`} />
    </Block>
  </section>
</Page>